59/*!
60 \class QFileDialog
61 \brief The QFileDialog class provides a dialog that allow users to select files or directories.
62 \ingroup standard-dialogs
63 \inmodule QtWidgets
64
65 The QFileDialog class enables a user to traverse the file system in
66 order to select one or many files or a directory.
67
68 The easiest way to create a QFileDialog is to use the static functions.
69
70 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 0
71
72 In the above example, a modal QFileDialog is created using a static
73 function. The dialog initially displays the contents of the "/home/jana"
74 directory, and displays files matching the patterns given in the
75 string "Image Files (*.png *.jpg *.bmp)". The parent of the file dialog
76 is set to \e this, and the window title is set to "Open Image".
77
78 If you want to use multiple filters, separate each one with
79 \e two semicolons. For example:
80
81 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 1
82
83 You can create your own QFileDialog without using the static
84 functions. By calling setFileMode(), you can specify what the user must
85 select in the dialog:
86
87 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 2
88
89 In the above example, the mode of the file dialog is set to
90 AnyFile, meaning that the user can select any file, or even specify a
91 file that doesn't exist. This mode is useful for creating a
92 "Save As" file dialog. Use ExistingFile if the user must select an
93 existing file, or \l Directory if only a directory may be selected.
94 See the \l QFileDialog::FileMode enum for the complete list of modes.
95
96 The fileMode property contains the mode of operation for the dialog;
97 this indicates what types of objects the user is expected to select.
98 Use setNameFilter() to set the dialog's file filter. For example:
99
100 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 3
101
102 In the above example, the filter is set to \c{"Images (*.png *.xpm *.jpg)"},
103 this means that only files with the extension \c png, \c xpm,
104 or \c jpg will be shown in the QFileDialog. You can apply
105 several filters by using setNameFilters(). Use selectNameFilter() to select
106 one of the filters you've given as the file dialog's default filter.
107
108 The file dialog has two view modes: \l{QFileDialog::}{List} and
109 \l{QFileDialog::}{Detail}.
110 \l{QFileDialog::}{List} presents the contents of the current directory
111 as a list of file and directory names. \l{QFileDialog::}{Detail} also
112 displays a list of file and directory names, but provides additional
113 information alongside each name, such as the file size and modification
114 date. Set the mode with setViewMode():
115
116 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 4
117
118 The last important function you will need to use when creating your
119 own file dialog is selectedFiles().
120
121 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 5
122
123 In the above example, a modal file dialog is created and shown. If
124 the user clicked OK, the file they selected is put in \c fileName.
125
126 The dialog's working directory can be set with setDirectory().
127 Each file in the current directory can be selected using
128 the selectFile() function.
129
130 The \l{dialogs/standarddialogs}{Standard Dialogs} example shows
131 how to use QFileDialog as well as other built-in Qt dialogs.
132
133 By default, a platform-native file dialog will be used if the platform has
134 one. In that case, the widgets which would otherwise be used to construct the
135 dialog will not be instantiated, so related accessors such as layout() and
136 itemDelegate() will return null. Also, not all platforms show file dialogs
137 with a title bar, so be aware that the caption text might not be visible to
138 the user. You can set the \l DontUseNativeDialog option to ensure that the
139 widget-based implementation will be used instead of the native dialog.
140
141 \sa QDir, QFileInfo, QFile, QColorDialog, QFontDialog, {Standard Dialogs Example},
142 {Qt Widgets - Application Example}
143*/
144
145/*!
146 \enum QFileDialog::AcceptMode
147
148 \value AcceptOpen
149 \value AcceptSave
150*/
151
152/*!
153 \enum QFileDialog::ViewMode
154
155 This enum describes the view mode of the file dialog; i.e. what
156 information about each file will be displayed.
157
158 \value Detail Displays an icon, a name, and details for each item in
159 the directory.
160 \value List Displays only an icon and a name for each item in the
161 directory.
162
163 \sa setViewMode()
164*/
165
166/*!
167 \enum QFileDialog::FileMode
168
169 This enum is used to indicate what the user may select in the file
170 dialog; i.e. what the dialog will return if the user clicks OK.
171
172 \value AnyFile The name of a file, whether it exists or not.
173 \value ExistingFile The name of a single existing file.
174 \value Directory The name of a directory. Both files and
175 directories are displayed. However, the native Windows
176 file dialog does not support displaying files in the
177 directory chooser.
178 \value ExistingFiles The names of zero or more existing files.
179
180 \sa setFileMode()
181*/
182
183/*!
184 \enum QFileDialog::Option
185
186 \value ShowDirsOnly Only show directories in the file dialog. By
187 default both files and directories are shown. (Valid only in the
188 \l Directory file mode.)
189
190 \value DontResolveSymlinks Don't resolve symlinks in the file
191 dialog. By default symlinks are resolved.
192
193 \value DontConfirmOverwrite Don't ask for confirmation if an
194 existing file is selected. By default confirmation is requested.
195
196 Note: This option is not supported on macOS when using the
197 native file dialog.
198
199 \value DontUseNativeDialog Don't use the native file dialog. By
200 default, the native file dialog is used unless you use a subclass
201 of QFileDialog that contains the Q_OBJECT macro, or the platform
202 does not have a native dialog of the type that you require.
203
204 \b{Note:} This option must be set before changing dialog properties
205 or showing the dialog.
206
207 \value ReadOnly Indicates that the model is readonly.
208
209 \value HideNameFilterDetails Indicates if the file name filter details are
210 hidden or not.
211
212 \value DontUseCustomDirectoryIcons Always use the default directory icon.
213 Some platforms allow the user to set a different icon. Custom icon lookup
214 cause a big performance impact over network or removable drives.
215 Setting this will enable the QFileIconProvider::DontUseCustomDirectoryIcons
216 option in the icon provider. This enum value was added in Qt 5.2.
217*/
218

406static const qint32 QFileDialogMagic = 0xbe;
407
408/*!
409 \since 4.3
410 Saves the state of the dialog's layout, history and current directory.
411
412 Typically this is used in conjunction with QSettings to remember the size
413 for a future session. A version number is stored as part of the data.
414*/
415QByteArray QFileDialog::saveState() const
416{
417 Q_D(const QFileDialog);
418 int version = 4;
419 QByteArray data;
420 QDataStream stream(&data, QIODevice::WriteOnly);
421 stream.setVersion(QDataStream::Qt_5_0);
422
423 stream << qint32(QFileDialogMagic);
424 stream << qint32(version);
425 if (d->usingWidgets()) {
426 stream << d->qFileDialogUi->splitter->saveState();
427 stream << d->qFileDialogUi->sidebar->urls();
428 } else {
429 stream << d->splitterState;
430 stream << d->sidebarUrls;
431 }
432 stream << history();
433 stream << *lastVisitedDir();
434 if (d->usingWidgets())
435 stream << d->qFileDialogUi->treeView->header()->saveState();
436 else
437 stream << d->headerData;
438 stream << qint32(viewMode());
439 return data;
440}
441
442/*!
443 \since 4.3
444 Restores the dialogs's layout, history and current directory to the \a state specified.
445
446 Typically this is used in conjunction with QSettings to restore the size
447 from a past session.
448
449 Returns \c false if there are errors
450*/
451bool QFileDialog::restoreState(const QByteArray &state)
452{
453 Q_D(QFileDialog);
454 QByteArray sd = state;
455 QDataStream stream(&sd, QIODevice::ReadOnly);
456 stream.setVersion(QDataStream::Qt_5_0);
457 if (stream.atEnd())
458 return false;
459 QStringList history;
460 QUrl currentDirectory;
461 qint32 marker;
462 qint32 v;
463 qint32 viewMode;
464 stream >> marker;
465 stream >> v;
466 // the code below only supports versions 3 and 4
467 if (marker != QFileDialogMagic || (v != 3 && v != 4))
468 return false;
469
470 stream >> d->splitterState
471 >> d->sidebarUrls
472 >> history;
473 if (v == 3) {
474 QString currentDirectoryString;
475 stream >> currentDirectoryString;
476 currentDirectory = QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: currentDirectoryString);
477 } else {
478 stream >> currentDirectory;
479 }
480 stream >> d->headerData
481 >> viewMode;
482
483 setDirectoryUrl(lastVisitedDir()->isEmpty() ? currentDirectory : *lastVisitedDir());
484 setViewMode(static_cast<QFileDialog::ViewMode>(viewMode));
485
486 if (!d->usingWidgets())
487 return true;
488
489 return d->restoreWidgetState(history, splitterPosition: -1);
490}

525void QFileDialogPrivate::initHelper(QPlatformDialogHelper *h)
526{
527 QFileDialog *d = q_func();
528 QObject::connect(sender: h, SIGNAL(fileSelected(QUrl)), receiver: d, SLOT(_q_emitUrlSelected(QUrl)));
529 QObject::connect(sender: h, SIGNAL(filesSelected(QList<QUrl>)), receiver: d, SLOT(_q_emitUrlsSelected(QList<QUrl>)));
530 QObject::connect(sender: h, SIGNAL(currentChanged(QUrl)), receiver: d, SLOT(_q_nativeCurrentChanged(QUrl)));
531 QObject::connect(sender: h, SIGNAL(directoryEntered(QUrl)), receiver: d, SLOT(_q_nativeEnterDirectory(QUrl)));
532 QObject::connect(sender: h, SIGNAL(filterSelected(QString)), receiver: d, SIGNAL(filterSelected(QString)));
533 static_cast<QPlatformFileDialogHelper *>(h)->setOptions(options);
534}

536void QFileDialogPrivate::helperPrepareShow(QPlatformDialogHelper *)
537{
538 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
539 options->setWindowTitle(q->windowTitle());
540 options->setHistory(q->history());
541 if (usingWidgets())
542 options->setSidebarUrls(qFileDialogUi->sidebar->urls());
543 if (options->initiallySelectedNameFilter().isEmpty())
544 options->setInitiallySelectedNameFilter(q->selectedNameFilter());
545 if (options->initiallySelectedFiles().isEmpty())
546 options->setInitiallySelectedFiles(userSelectedFiles());
547}
548
549void QFileDialogPrivate::helperDone(QDialog::DialogCode code, QPlatformDialogHelper *)
550{
551 if (code == QDialog::Accepted) {
552 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
553 q->setViewMode(static_cast<QFileDialog::ViewMode>(options->viewMode()));
554 q->setSidebarUrls(options->sidebarUrls());
555 q->setHistory(options->history());
556 }
557}

559void QFileDialogPrivate::retranslateWindowTitle()
560{
561 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
562 if (!useDefaultCaption || setWindowTitle != q->windowTitle())
563 return;
564 if (q->acceptMode() == QFileDialog::AcceptOpen) {
565 const QFileDialog::FileMode fileMode = q->fileMode();
566 if (fileMode == QFileDialog::Directory)
567 q->setWindowTitle(QFileDialog::tr(s: "Find Directory"));
568 else
569 q->setWindowTitle(QFileDialog::tr(s: "Open"));
570 } else
571 q->setWindowTitle(QFileDialog::tr(s: "Save As"));
572
573 setWindowTitle = q->windowTitle();
574}

587void QFileDialogPrivate::updateFileNameLabel()
588{
589 if (options->isLabelExplicitlySet(label: QFileDialogOptions::FileName)) {
590 setLabelTextControl(label: QFileDialog::FileName, text: options->labelText(label: QFileDialogOptions::FileName));
591 } else {
592 switch (q_func()->fileMode()) {
593 case QFileDialog::Directory:
594 setLabelTextControl(label: QFileDialog::FileName, text: QFileDialog::tr(s: "Directory:"));
595 break;
596 default:
597 setLabelTextControl(label: QFileDialog::FileName, text: QFileDialog::tr(s: "File &name:"));
598 break;
599 }
600 }
601}

608
609void QFileDialogPrivate::updateOkButtonText(bool saveAsOnFolder)
610{
611 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
612 // 'Save as' at a folder: Temporarily change to "Open".
613 if (saveAsOnFolder) {
614 setLabelTextControl(label: QFileDialog::Accept, text: QFileDialog::tr(s: "&Open"));
615 } else if (options->isLabelExplicitlySet(label: QFileDialogOptions::Accept)) {
616 setLabelTextControl(label: QFileDialog::Accept, text: options->labelText(label: QFileDialogOptions::Accept));
617 return;
618 } else {
619 switch (q->fileMode()) {
620 case QFileDialog::Directory:
621 setLabelTextControl(label: QFileDialog::Accept, text: QFileDialog::tr(s: "&Choose"));
622 break;
623 default:
624 setLabelTextControl(label: QFileDialog::Accept,
625 text: q->acceptMode() == QFileDialog::AcceptOpen ?
626 QFileDialog::tr(s: "&Open") :
627 QFileDialog::tr(s: "&Save"));
628 break;
629 }
630 }
631}

638
639void QFileDialogPrivate::retranslateStrings()
640{
641 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
642 /* WIDGETS */
643 if (options->useDefaultNameFilters())
644 q->setNameFilter(QFileDialogOptions::defaultNameFilterString());
645 if (!usingWidgets())
646 return;
647
648 QList<QAction*> actions = qFileDialogUi->treeView->header()->actions();
649 QAbstractItemModel *abstractModel = model;
650#if QT_CONFIG(proxymodel)
651 if (proxyModel)
652 abstractModel = proxyModel;
653#endif
654 int total = qMin(a: abstractModel->columnCount(parent: QModelIndex()), b: actions.size() + 1);
655 for (int i = 1; i < total; ++i) {
656 actions.at(i: i - 1)->setText(QFileDialog::tr(s: "Show ") + abstractModel->headerData(section: i, orientation: Qt::Horizontal, role: Qt::DisplayRole).toString());
657 }
658
659 /* MENU ACTIONS */
660 renameAction->setText(QFileDialog::tr(s: "&Rename"));
661 deleteAction->setText(QFileDialog::tr(s: "&Delete"));
662 showHiddenAction->setText(QFileDialog::tr(s: "Show &hidden files"));
663 newFolderAction->setText(QFileDialog::tr(s: "&New Folder"));
664 qFileDialogUi->retranslateUi(q);
665 updateLookInLabel();
666 updateFileNameLabel();
667 updateFileTypeLabel();
668 updateCancelButtonText();
669}

671void QFileDialogPrivate::emitFilesSelected(const QStringList &files)
672{
673 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
674 emit q->filesSelected(files);
675 if (files.size() == 1)
676 emit q->fileSelected(file: files.first());
677}
678
679bool QFileDialogPrivate::canBeNativeDialog() const
680{
681 // Don't use Q_Q here! This function is called from ~QDialog,
682 // so Q_Q calling q_func() invokes undefined behavior (invalid cast in q_func()).
683 const QDialog * const q = static_cast<const QDialog*>(q_ptr);
684 if (nativeDialogInUse)
685 return true;
686 if (QCoreApplication::testAttribute(attribute: Qt::AA_DontUseNativeDialogs)
687 || q->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_DontShowOnScreen)
688 || (options->options() & QFileDialog::DontUseNativeDialog)) {
689 return false;
690 }
691
692 return strcmp(s1: QFileDialog::staticMetaObject.className(), s2: q->metaObject()->className()) == 0;
693}
694
695bool QFileDialogPrivate::usingWidgets() const
696{
697 return !nativeDialogInUse && qFileDialogUi;
698}

700/*!
701 \since 4.5
702 Sets the given \a option to be enabled if \a on is true; otherwise,
703 clears the given \a option.
704
705 Options (particularly the DontUseNativeDialogs option) should be set
706 before changing dialog properties or showing the dialog.
707
708 Setting options while the dialog is visible is not guaranteed to have
709 an immediate effect on the dialog (depending on the option and on the
710 platform).
711
712 Setting options after changing other properties may cause these
713 values to have no effect.
714
715 \sa options, testOption()
716*/
717void QFileDialog::setOption(Option option, bool on)
718{
719 const QFileDialog::Options previousOptions = options();
720 if (!(previousOptions & option) != !on)
721 setOptions(previousOptions ^ option);
722}
723
724/*!
725 \since 4.5
726
727 Returns \c true if the given \a option is enabled; otherwise, returns
728 false.
729
730 \sa options, setOption()
731*/
732bool QFileDialog::testOption(Option option) const
733{
734 Q_D(const QFileDialog);
735 return d->options->testOption(option: static_cast<QFileDialogOptions::FileDialogOption>(option));
736}

738/*!
739 \property QFileDialog::options
740 \brief the various options that affect the look and feel of the dialog
741 \since 4.5
742
743 By default, all options are disabled.
744
745 Options (particularly the DontUseNativeDialogs option) should be set
746 before changing dialog properties or showing the dialog.
747
748 Setting options while the dialog is visible is not guaranteed to have
749 an immediate effect on the dialog (depending on the option and on the
750 platform).
751
752 Setting options after changing other properties may cause these
753 values to have no effect.
754
755 \sa setOption(), testOption()
756*/
757void QFileDialog::setOptions(Options options)
758{
759 Q_D(QFileDialog);
760
761 Options changed = (options ^ QFileDialog::options());
762 if (!changed)
763 return;
764
765 d->options->setOptions(QFileDialogOptions::FileDialogOptions(int(options)));
766
767 if (options & DontUseNativeDialog) {
768 d->nativeDialogInUse = false;
769 d->createWidgets();
770 }
771
772 if (d->usingWidgets()) {
773 if (changed & DontResolveSymlinks)
774 d->model->setResolveSymlinks(!(options & DontResolveSymlinks));
775 if (changed & ReadOnly) {
776 bool ro = (options & ReadOnly);
777 d->model->setReadOnly(ro);
778 d->qFileDialogUi->newFolderButton->setEnabled(!ro);
779 d->renameAction->setEnabled(!ro);
780 d->deleteAction->setEnabled(!ro);
781 }
782
783 if (changed & DontUseCustomDirectoryIcons) {
784 QFileIconProvider::Options providerOptions = iconProvider()->options();
785 providerOptions.setFlag(flag: QFileIconProvider::DontUseCustomDirectoryIcons,
786 on: options & DontUseCustomDirectoryIcons);
787 iconProvider()->setOptions(providerOptions);
788 }
789 }
790
791 if (changed & HideNameFilterDetails)
792 setNameFilters(d->options->nameFilters());
793
794 if (changed & ShowDirsOnly)
795 setFilter((options & ShowDirsOnly) ? filter() & ~QDir::Files : filter() | QDir::Files);
796}

1007{

1011 // file system mounted, wrongly capitalized drive letters will cause mismatches.
1012 return false;
1013#elif defined(Q_OS_MACOS)

1020// Determine the file name to be set on the line edit from the path
1021// passed to selectFile() in mode QFileDialog::AcceptSave.
1022static inline QString fileFromPath(const QString &rootPath, QString path)
1023{
1024 if (!QFileInfo(path).isAbsolute())
1025 return path;
1026 if (path.startsWith(s: rootPath, cs: isCaseSensitiveFileSystem(path: rootPath) ? Qt::CaseSensitive : Qt::CaseInsensitive))
1027 path.remove(i: 0, len: rootPath.size());
1028
1029 if (path.isEmpty())
1030 return path;
1031
1032 if (path.at(i: 0) == QDir::separator()
1033#ifdef Q_OS_WIN
1034 //On Windows both cases can happen
1035 || path.at(0) == u'/'
1036#endif
1037 ) {
1038 path.remove(i: 0, len: 1);
1039 }
1040 return path;
1041}

1043/*!
1044 Selects the given \a filename in the file dialog.
1045
1046 \sa selectedFiles()
1047*/
1048void QFileDialog::selectFile(const QString &filename)
1049{
1050 Q_D(QFileDialog);
1051 if (filename.isEmpty())
1052 return;
1053
1054 if (!d->usingWidgets()) {
1055 QUrl url;
1056 if (QFileInfo(filename).isRelative()) {
1057 url = d->options->initialDirectory();
1058 QString path = url.path();
1059 if (!path.endsWith(c: u'/'))
1060 path += u'/';
1061 url.setPath(path: path + filename);
1062 } else {
1063 url = QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: filename);
1064 }
1065 d->selectFile_sys(filename: url);
1066 d->options->setInitiallySelectedFiles(QList<QUrl>() << url);
1067 return;
1068 }
1069
1070 if (!QDir::isRelativePath(path: filename)) {
1071 QFileInfo info(filename);
1072 QString filenamePath = info.absoluteDir().path();
1073
1074 if (d->model->rootPath() != filenamePath)
1075 setDirectory(filenamePath);
1076 }
1077
1078 QModelIndex index = d->model->index(path: filename);
1079 d->qFileDialogUi->listView->selectionModel()->clear();
1080 if (!isVisible() || !d->lineEdit()->hasFocus())
1081 d->lineEdit()->setText(index.isValid() ? index.data().toString() : fileFromPath(rootPath: d->rootPath(), path: filename));
1082}

1107Q_AUTOTEST_EXPORT QString qt_tildeExpansion(const QString &path)
1108{
1109 if (!path.startsWith(c: u'~'))
1110 return path;

1112 if (separatorPosition < 0)

1118 const QString homePath = QDir::homePath();
1119#else

1121# if defined(_POSIX_THREAD_SAFE_FUNCTIONS) && !defined(Q_OS_OPENBSD) && !defined(Q_OS_WASM)
1122 passwd pw;
1123 passwd *tmpPw;

1128 tmpPw = getpwnam_r(userName.constData(), &pw, buf, bufSize);
1129# else
1130 err = getpwnam_r(name: userName.constData(), resultbuf: &pw, buffer: buf, buflen: bufSize, result: &tmpPw);
1131# endif
1132 if (err || !tmpPw)
1133 return path;
1134 const QString homePath = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: pw.pw_dir);
1135# else

1137 if (!pw)
1138 return path;
1139 const QString homePath = QString::fromLocal8Bit(pw->pw_dir);
1140# endif

1147/**
1148 Returns the text in the line edit which can be one or more file names
1149 */
1150QStringList QFileDialogPrivate::typedFiles() const
1151{
1152 Q_Q(const QFileDialog);
1153 QStringList files;
1154 QString editText = lineEdit()->text();
1155 if (!editText.contains(c: u'"')) {
1156#ifdef Q_OS_UNIX
1157 const QString prefix = q->directory().absolutePath() + QDir::separator();
1158 if (QFile::exists(fileName: prefix + editText))
1159 files << editText;
1160 else
1161 files << qt_tildeExpansion(path: editText);
1162#else
1163 files << editText;
1164 Q_UNUSED(q);
1165#endif
1166 } else {
1167 // " is used to separate files like so: "file1" "file2" "file3" ...
1168 // ### need escape character for filenames with quotes (")
1169 QStringList tokens = editText.split(sep: u'\"');
1170 for (int i=0; i<tokens.size(); ++i) {
1171 if ((i % 2) == 0)
1172 continue; // Every even token is a separator
1173#ifdef Q_OS_UNIX
1174 const QString token = tokens.at(i);
1175 const QString prefix = q->directory().absolutePath() + QDir::separator();
1176 if (QFile::exists(fileName: prefix + token))
1177 files << token;
1178 else
1179 files << qt_tildeExpansion(path: token);
1180#else
1181 files << toInternal(tokens.at(i));
1182#endif
1183 }
1184 }
1185 return addDefaultSuffixToFiles(filesToFix: files);
1186}

1188// Return selected files without defaulting to the root of the file system model
1189// used for initializing QFileDialogOptions for native dialogs. The default is
1190// not suitable for native dialogs since it mostly equals directory().
1191QList<QUrl> QFileDialogPrivate::userSelectedFiles() const
1192{
1193 QList<QUrl> files;
1194
1195 if (!usingWidgets())
1196 return addDefaultSuffixToUrls(urlsToFix: selectedFiles_sys());
1197
1198 const QModelIndexList selectedRows = qFileDialogUi->listView->selectionModel()->selectedRows();
1199 files.reserve(size: selectedRows.size());
1200 for (const QModelIndex &index : selectedRows)
1201 files.append(t: QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: index.data(arole: QFileSystemModel::FilePathRole).toString()));
1202
1203 if (files.isEmpty() && !lineEdit()->text().isEmpty()) {
1204 const QStringList typedFilesList = typedFiles();
1205 files.reserve(size: typedFilesList.size());
1206 for (const QString &path : typedFilesList)
1207 files.append(t: QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: path));
1208 }
1209
1210 return files;
1211}

1213QStringList QFileDialogPrivate::addDefaultSuffixToFiles(const QStringList &filesToFix) const
1214{
1215 QStringList files;
1216 for (int i=0; i<filesToFix.size(); ++i) {
1217 QString name = toInternal(path: filesToFix.at(i));
1218 QFileInfo info(name);
1219 // if the filename has no suffix, add the default suffix
1220 const QString defaultSuffix = options->defaultSuffix();
1221 if (!defaultSuffix.isEmpty() && !info.isDir() && !info.fileName().contains(c: u'.'))
1222 name += u'.' + defaultSuffix;
1223
1224 if (info.isAbsolute()) {
1225 files.append(t: name);
1226 } else {
1227 // at this point the path should only have Qt path separators.
1228 // This check is needed since we might be at the root directory
1229 // and on Windows it already ends with slash.
1230 QString path = rootPath();
1231 if (!path.endsWith(c: u'/'))
1232 path += u'/';
1233 path += name;
1234 files.append(t: path);
1235 }
1236 }
1237 return files;
1238}

1240QList<QUrl> QFileDialogPrivate::addDefaultSuffixToUrls(const QList<QUrl> &urlsToFix) const
1241{
1242 QList<QUrl> urls;
1243 const int numUrlsToFix = urlsToFix.size();
1244 urls.reserve(size: numUrlsToFix);
1245 for (int i = 0; i < numUrlsToFix; ++i) {
1246 QUrl url = urlsToFix.at(i);
1247 // if the filename has no suffix, add the default suffix
1248 const QString defaultSuffix = options->defaultSuffix();
1249 if (!defaultSuffix.isEmpty()) {
1250 const QString urlPath = url.path();
1251 const auto idx = urlPath.lastIndexOf(c: u'/');
1252 if (idx != (urlPath.size() - 1) && !QStringView{urlPath}.mid(pos: idx + 1).contains(c: u'.'))
1253 url.setPath(path: urlPath + u'.' + defaultSuffix);
1254 }
1255 urls.append(t: url);
1256 }
1257 return urls;
1258}

1309/*
1310 Makes a list of filters from ;;-separated text.
1311 Used by the mac and windows implementations
1312*/
1313QStringList qt_make_filter_list(const QString &filter)
1314{
1315 if (filter.isEmpty())
1316 return QStringList();
1317
1318 auto sep = ";;"_L1;
1319 if (!filter.contains(s: sep) && filter.contains(c: u'\n'))
1320 sep = "\n"_L1;
1321
1322 return filter.split(sep);
1323}

1349 Strip the filters by removing the details, e.g. (*.*).
1350*/
1351QStringList qt_strip_filters(const QStringList &filters)
1352{
1353#if QT_CONFIG(regularexpression)
1354 QStringList strippedFilters;
1355 static const QRegularExpression r(QString::fromLatin1(ba: QPlatformFileDialogHelper::filterRegExp));
1356 const int numFilters = filters.size();
1357 strippedFilters.reserve(size: numFilters);

1372/*!
1373 \since 4.4
1374
1375 Sets the \a filters used in the file dialog.
1376
1377 Note that the filter \b{*.*} is not portable, because the historical
1378 assumption that the file extension determines the file type is not
1379 consistent on every operating system. It is possible to have a file with no
1380 dot in its name (for example, \c Makefile). In a native Windows file
1381 dialog, \b{*.*} will match such files, while in other types of file dialogs
1382 it may not. So it is better to use \b{*} if you mean to select any file.
1383
1384 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 7
1385
1386 \l setMimeTypeFilters() has the advantage of providing all possible name
1387 filters for each file type. For example, JPEG images have three possible
1388 extensions; if your application can open such files, selecting the
1389 \c image/jpeg mime type as a filter will allow you to open all of them.
1390*/
1391void QFileDialog::setNameFilters(const QStringList &filters)
1392{
1393 Q_D(QFileDialog);
1394 QStringList cleanedFilters;
1395 const int numFilters = filters.size();
1396 cleanedFilters.reserve(size: numFilters);
1397 for (int i = 0; i < numFilters; ++i) {
1398 cleanedFilters << filters[i].simplified();
1399 }
1400 d->options->setNameFilters(cleanedFilters);
1401
1402 if (!d->usingWidgets())
1403 return;
1404
1405 d->qFileDialogUi->fileTypeCombo->clear();
1406 if (cleanedFilters.isEmpty())
1407 return;
1408
1409 if (testOption(option: HideNameFilterDetails))
1410 d->qFileDialogUi->fileTypeCombo->addItems(qt_strip_filters(filters: cleanedFilters));
1411 else

1949void QFileDialogPrivate::setLabelTextControl(QFileDialog::DialogLabel label, const QString &text)
1950{
1951 if (!qFileDialogUi)
1952 return;
1953 switch (label) {
1954 case QFileDialog::LookIn:
1955 qFileDialogUi->lookInLabel->setText(text);
1956 break;
1957 case QFileDialog::FileName:
1958 qFileDialogUi->fileNameLabel->setText(text);
1959 break;
1960 case QFileDialog::FileType:
1961 qFileDialogUi->fileTypeLabel->setText(text);
1962 break;
1963 case QFileDialog::Accept:
1964 if (q_func()->acceptMode() == QFileDialog::AcceptOpen) {
1965 if (QPushButton *button = qFileDialogUi->buttonBox->button(QDialogButtonBox::Open))
1966 button->setText(text);
1967 } else {
1968 if (QPushButton *button = qFileDialogUi->buttonBox->button(QDialogButtonBox::Save))
1969 button->setText(text);
1970 }
1971 break;
1972 case QFileDialog::Reject:
1973 if (QPushButton *button = qFileDialogUi->buttonBox->button(QDialogButtonBox::Cancel))
1974 button->setText(text);
1975 break;
1976 }
1977}

1994{
1995 Q_D(const QFileDialog);
1996 if (!d->usingWidgets())
1997 return d->options->labelText(label: static_cast<QFileDialogOptions::DialogLabel>(label));
1998 QPushButton *button;
1999 switch (label) {
2000 case LookIn:

2002 case FileName:
2003 return d->qFileDialogUi->fileNameLabel->text();
2004 case FileType:

2009 else

2012 return button->text();
2013 break;
2014 case Reject:
2015 button = d->qFileDialogUi->buttonBox->button(QDialogButtonBox::Cancel);
2016 if (button)
2017 return button->text();
2018 break;

2023/*!
2024 This is a convenience static function that returns an existing file
2025 selected by the user. If the user presses Cancel, it returns a null string.
2026
2027 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 8
2028
2029 The function creates a modal file dialog with the given \a parent widget.
2030 If \a parent is not \nullptr, the dialog will be shown centered over the
2031 parent widget.
2032
2033 The file dialog's working directory will be set to \a dir. If \a dir
2034 includes a file name, the file will be selected. Only files that match the
2035 given \a filter are shown. The filter selected is set to \a selectedFilter.
2036 The parameters \a dir, \a selectedFilter, and \a filter may be empty
2037 strings. If you want multiple filters, separate them with ';;', for
2038 example:
2039
2040 \snippet code/src_gui_dialogs_qfiledialog.cpp 14
2041
2042 The \a options argument holds various options about how to run the dialog,
2043 see the QFileDialog::Option enum for more information on the flags you can
2044 pass.
2045
2046 The dialog's caption is set to \a caption. If \a caption is not specified
2047 then a default caption will be used.
2048
2049 On Windows, and \macos, this static function will use the
2050 native file dialog and not a QFileDialog. Note that the \macos native file
2051 dialog does not show a title bar.
2052
2053 On Windows the dialog will spin a blocking modal event loop that will not
2054 dispatch any QTimers, and if \a parent is not \nullptr then it will position
2055 the dialog just below the parent's title bar.
2056
2057 On Unix/X11, the normal behavior of the file dialog is to resolve and
2058 follow symlinks. For example, if \c{/usr/tmp} is a symlink to \c{/var/tmp},
2059 the file dialog will change to \c{/var/tmp} after entering \c{/usr/tmp}. If
2060 \a options includes DontResolveSymlinks, the file dialog will treat
2061 symlinks as regular directories.
2062
2063 \warning Do not delete \a parent during the execution of the dialog. If you
2064 want to do this, you should create the dialog yourself using one of the
2065 QFileDialog constructors.
2066
2067 \sa getOpenFileNames(), getSaveFileName(), getExistingDirectory()
2068*/
2069QString QFileDialog::getOpenFileName(QWidget *parent,
2070 const QString &caption,
2071 const QString &dir,
2072 const QString &filter,
2073 QString *selectedFilter,
2074 Options options)
2075{
2076 const QStringList schemes = QStringList(QStringLiteral("file"));
2077 const QUrl selectedUrl = getOpenFileUrl(parent, caption, dir: QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: dir), filter,
2078 selectedFilter, options, supportedSchemes: schemes);
2079 if (selectedUrl.isLocalFile() || selectedUrl.isEmpty())
2080 return selectedUrl.toLocalFile();
2081 else
2082 return selectedUrl.toString();
2083}
2084
2085/*!
2086 This is a convenience static function that returns an existing file
2087 selected by the user. If the user presses Cancel, it returns an
2088 empty url.
2089
2090 The function is used similarly to QFileDialog::getOpenFileName(). In
2091 particular \a parent, \a caption, \a dir, \a filter, \a selectedFilter
2092 and \a options are used in the exact same way.
2093
2094 The main difference with QFileDialog::getOpenFileName() comes from
2095 the ability offered to the user to select a remote file. That's why
2096 the return type and the type of \a dir is QUrl.
2097
2098 The \a supportedSchemes argument allows to restrict the type of URLs the
2099 user will be able to select. It is a way for the application to declare
2100 the protocols it will support to fetch the file content. An empty list
2101 means that no restriction is applied (the default).
2102 Supported for local files ("file" scheme) is implicit and always enabled;
2103 it is not necessary to include it in the restriction.
2104

2596inline static QUrl _qt_get_directory(const QUrl &url, const QFileInfo &local)
2597{
2598 if (url.isLocalFile()) {
2599 QFileInfo info = local;
2600 if (!local.isAbsolute())
2601 info = QFileInfo(QDir::current(), url.toLocalFile());
2602 const QFileInfo pathInfo(info.absolutePath());
2603 if (!pathInfo.exists() || !pathInfo.isDir())
2604 return QUrl();
2605 if (info.exists() && info.isDir())
2606 return QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: QDir::cleanPath(path: info.absoluteFilePath()));
2607 return QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: pathInfo.absoluteFilePath());
2608 } else {
2609 return url;
2610 }
2611}

2613/*
2614 Initialize working directory and selection from \a url.
2615*/
2616QFileDialogArgs::QFileDialogArgs(const QUrl &url)
2617{
2618 // default case, re-use QFileInfo to avoid stat'ing
2619 const QFileInfo local(url.toLocalFile());
2620 // Get the initial directory URL
2621 if (!url.isEmpty())
2622 directory = _qt_get_directory(url, local);
2623 if (directory.isEmpty()) {
2624 const QUrl lastVisited = *lastVisitedDir();
2625 if (lastVisited != url)
2626 directory = _qt_get_directory(url: lastVisited, local: QFileInfo());
2627 }
2628 if (directory.isEmpty())
2629 directory = QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: QDir::currentPath());
2630
2631 /*
2632 The initial directory can contain both the initial directory
2633 and initial selection, e.g. /home/user/foo.txt
2634 */
2635 if (selection.isEmpty() && !url.isEmpty()) {
2636 if (url.isLocalFile()) {
2637 if (!local.isDir())
2638 selection = local.fileName();
2639 } else {
2640 // With remote URLs we can only assume.
2641 selection = url.fileName();
2642 }
2643 }
2644}

2690/*!
2691 \reimp
2692*/
2693void QFileDialog::accept()
2694{
2695 Q_D(QFileDialog);
2696 if (!d->usingWidgets()) {
2697 const QList<QUrl> urls = selectedUrls();
2698 if (urls.isEmpty())
2699 return;
2700 d->_q_emitUrlsSelected(files: urls);
2701 if (urls.size() == 1)
2702 d->_q_emitUrlSelected(file: urls.first());
2703 QDialog::accept();
2704 return;
2705 }
2706
2707 const QStringList files = selectedFiles();
2708 if (files.isEmpty())
2709 return;
2710 QString lineEditText = d->lineEdit()->text();
2711 // "hidden feature" type .. and then enter, and it will move up a dir
2712 // special case for ".."
2713 if (lineEditText == ".."_L1) {
2714 d->_q_navigateToParent();
2715 const QSignalBlocker blocker(d->qFileDialogUi->fileNameEdit);
2716 d->lineEdit()->selectAll();
2717 return;
2718 }
2719
2720 const auto mode = fileMode();
2721 switch (mode) {
2722 case Directory: {
2723 QString fn = files.first();
2724 QFileInfo info(fn);
2725 if (!info.exists())
2726 info = QFileInfo(d->getEnvironmentVariable(string: fn));
2727 if (!info.exists()) {
2728 d->itemNotFound(fileName: info.fileName(), mode);
2729 return;
2730 }
2731 if (info.isDir()) {
2732 d->emitFilesSelected(files);
2733 QDialog::accept();
2734 }
2735 return;
2736 }
2737
2738 case AnyFile: {
2739 QString fn = files.first();
2740 QFileInfo info(fn);
2741 if (info.isDir()) {
2742 setDirectory(info.absoluteFilePath());
2743 return;
2744 }
2745
2746 if (!info.exists()) {
2747 int maxNameLength = d->maxNameLength(path: info.path());
2748 if (maxNameLength >= 0 && info.fileName().size() > maxNameLength)
2749 return;
2750 }
2751
2752 // check if we have to ask for permission to overwrite the file
2753 if (!info.exists() || testOption(option: DontConfirmOverwrite) || acceptMode() == AcceptOpen) {
2754 d->emitFilesSelected(files: QStringList(fn));
2755 QDialog::accept();
2756 } else {
2757 if (d->itemAlreadyExists(fileName: info.fileName())) {
2758 d->emitFilesSelected(files: QStringList(fn));
2759 QDialog::accept();
2760 }
2761 }
2762 return;
2763 }
2764
2765 case ExistingFile:
2766 case ExistingFiles:
2767 for (const auto &file : files) {
2768 QFileInfo info(file);
2769 if (!info.exists())
2770 info = QFileInfo(d->getEnvironmentVariable(string: file));
2771 if (!info.exists()) {
2772 d->itemNotFound(fileName: info.fileName(), mode);
2773 return;
2774 }
2775 if (info.isDir()) {
2776 setDirectory(info.absoluteFilePath());
2777 d->lineEdit()->clear();
2778 return;
2779 }
2780 }
2781 d->emitFilesSelected(files);
2782 QDialog::accept();
2783 return;
2784 }
2785}

2847bool QFileDialogPrivate::restoreWidgetState(QStringList &history, int splitterPosition)
2848{
2849 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
2850 if (splitterPosition >= 0) {
2851 QList<int> splitterSizes;
2852 splitterSizes.append(t: splitterPosition);
2853 splitterSizes.append(qFileDialogUi->splitter->widget(1)->sizeHint().width());
2854 qFileDialogUi->splitter->setSizes(splitterSizes);
2855 } else {
2856 if (!qFileDialogUi->splitter->restoreState(splitterState))
2857 return false;
2858 QList<int> list = qFileDialogUi->splitter->sizes();
2859 if (list.size() >= 2 && (list.at(i: 0) == 0 || list.at(i: 1) == 0)) {
2860 for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); ++i)
2861 list[i] = qFileDialogUi->splitter->widget(i)->sizeHint().width();
2862 qFileDialogUi->splitter->setSizes(list);
2863 }
2864 }
2865
2866 qFileDialogUi->sidebar->setUrls(sidebarUrls);
2867
2868 static const int MaxHistorySize = 5;
2869 if (history.size() > MaxHistorySize)
2870 history.erase(begin: history.begin(), end: history.end() - MaxHistorySize);
2871 q->setHistory(history);
2872
2873 QHeaderView *headerView = qFileDialogUi->treeView->header();
2874 if (!headerView->restoreState(state: headerData))
2875 return false;
2876
2877 QList<QAction*> actions = headerView->actions();
2878 QAbstractItemModel *abstractModel = model;
2879#if QT_CONFIG(proxymodel)
2880 if (proxyModel)
2881 abstractModel = proxyModel;
2882#endif
2883 int total = qMin(a: abstractModel->columnCount(parent: QModelIndex()), b: actions.size() + 1);
2884 for (int i = 1; i < total; ++i)
2885 actions.at(i: i - 1)->setChecked(!headerView->isSectionHidden(logicalIndex: i));
2886
2887 return true;
2888}

3535/*!
3536 \internal
3537
3538 Deletes the currently selected item in the dialog.
3539*/
3540void QFileDialogPrivate::_q_deleteCurrent()
3541{
3542 if (model->isReadOnly())
3543 return;
3544
3545 QModelIndexList list = qFileDialogUi->listView->selectionModel()->selectedRows();
3546 for (int i = list.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
3547 QPersistentModelIndex index = list.at(i);
3548 if (index == qFileDialogUi->listView->rootIndex())
3549 continue;
3550
3551 index = mapToSource(index: index.sibling(row: index.row(), column: 0));
3552 if (!index.isValid())
3553 continue;
3554
3555 QString fileName = index.data(role: QFileSystemModel::FileNameRole).toString();
3556 QString filePath = index.data(role: QFileSystemModel::FilePathRole).toString();
3557
3558 QFile::Permissions p(index.parent().data(arole: QFileSystemModel::FilePermissions).toInt());
3559#if QT_CONFIG(messagebox)
3560 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
3561 if (!(p & QFile::WriteUser) && (QMessageBox::warning(parent: q_func(), title: QFileDialog::tr(s: "Delete"),
3562 text: QFileDialog::tr(s: "'%1' is write protected.\nDo you want to delete it anyway?")
3563 .arg(a: fileName),
3564 buttons: QMessageBox::Yes | QMessageBox::No, defaultButton: QMessageBox::No) == QMessageBox::No))
3565 return;
3566 else if (QMessageBox::warning(parent: q_func(), title: QFileDialog::tr(s: "Delete"),
3567 text: QFileDialog::tr(s: "Are you sure you want to delete '%1'?")
3568 .arg(a: fileName),
3569 buttons: QMessageBox::Yes | QMessageBox::No, defaultButton: QMessageBox::No) == QMessageBox::No)
3570 return;
3571
3572 // the event loop has run, we have to validate if the index is valid because the model might have removed it.
3573 if (!index.isValid())
3574 return;
3575
3576#else
3577 if (!(p & QFile::WriteUser))
3578 return;
3579#endif // QT_CONFIG(messagebox)
3580
3581 if (model->isDir(index) && !model->fileInfo(index).isSymLink()) {
3582 if (!removeDirectory(path: filePath)) {
3583#if QT_CONFIG(messagebox)
3584 QMessageBox::warning(parent: q, title: q->windowTitle(),
3585 text: QFileDialog::tr(s: "Could not delete directory."));
3586#endif
3587 }
3588 } else {
3589 model->remove(index);

3662 QModelIndex idx = model->index(path: fn);

3664 QString fileName;

3666 fileDir = info.canonicalFilePath();
3667 } else {
3668 fileDir = fn.mid(position: 0, n: fn.lastIndexOf(c: u'/'));
3669 fileName = fn.mid(position: fileDir.size() + 1);

3689 break;

3691 case QFileDialog::ExistingFile:

3693 for (const auto &file : files) {
3694 QModelIndex idx = model->index(path: file);
3695 if (!idx.isValid())
3696 idx = model->index(path: getEnvironmentVariable(string: file));
3697 if (!idx.isValid()) {

3702 isOpenDirectory = true;

3936/*!
3937 \internal
3938
3939 For the list and tree view watch keys to goto parent and back in the history
3940
3941 returns \c true if handled
3942*/
3943bool QFileDialogPrivate::itemViewKeyboardEvent(QKeyEvent *event) {
3944
3945#if QT_CONFIG(shortcut)
3946 Q_Q(QFileDialog);
3947 if (event->matches(key: QKeySequence::Cancel)) {
3948 q->reject();
3949 return true;
3950 }
3951#endif
3952 switch (event->key()) {
3953 case Qt::Key_Backspace:
3954 _q_navigateToParent();
3955 return true;
3956 case Qt::Key_Back:
3957#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
3958 if (QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled())
3959 return false;
3960#endif
3961 case Qt::Key_Left:
3962 if (event->key() == Qt::Key_Back || event->modifiers() == Qt::AltModifier) {
3963 _q_navigateBackward();
3964 return true;
3965 }
3966 break;
3967 default:
3968 break;
3969 }
3970 return false;
3971}

3995void QFileDialogComboBox::showPopup()
3996{
3997 if (model()->rowCount() > 1)
3998 QComboBox::showPopup();
3999
4000 urlModel->setUrls(QList<QUrl>());
4001 QList<QUrl> list;
4002 QModelIndex idx = d_ptr->model->index(path: d_ptr->rootPath());
4003 while (idx.isValid()) {
4004 QUrl url = QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: idx.data(arole: QFileSystemModel::FilePathRole).toString());
4005 if (url.isValid())
4006 list.append(t: url);
4007 idx = idx.parent();
4008 }
4009 // add "my computer"
4010 list.append(t: QUrl("file:"_L1));
4011 urlModel->addUrls(urls: list, row: 0);
4012 idx = model()->index(row: model()->rowCount() - 1, column: 0);
4013
4014 // append history
4015 QList<QUrl> urls;
4016 for (int i = 0; i < m_history.size(); ++i) {
4017 QUrl path = QUrl::fromLocalFile(localfile: m_history.at(i));
4018 if (!urls.contains(t: path))
4019 urls.prepend(t: path);
4020 }
4021 if (urls.size() > 0) {
4022 model()->insertRow(arow: model()->rowCount());
4023 idx = model()->index(row: model()->rowCount()-1, column: 0);
4024 // ### TODO maybe add a horizontal line before this
4025 model()->setData(index: idx, value: QFileDialog::tr(s: "Recent Places"));
4026 QStandardItemModel *m = qobject_cast<QStandardItemModel*>(object: model());
4027 if (m) {
4028 Qt::ItemFlags flags = m->flags(index: idx);
4029 flags &= ~Qt::ItemIsEnabled;
4030 m->item(row: idx.row(), column: idx.column())->setFlags(flags);
4031 }
4032 urlModel->addUrls(urls, row: -1, move: false);
4033 }
4034 setCurrentIndex(0);
4035
4036 QComboBox::showPopup();
4037}

4155QString QFSCompleter::pathFromIndex(const QModelIndex &index) const
4156{
4157 const QFileSystemModel *dirModel;
4158 if (proxyModel)
4159 dirModel = qobject_cast<const QFileSystemModel *>(object: proxyModel->sourceModel());
4160 else
4161 dirModel = sourceModel;
4162 QString currentLocation = dirModel->rootPath();
4163 QString path = index.data(arole: QFileSystemModel::FilePathRole).toString();
4164 if (!currentLocation.isEmpty() && path.startsWith(s: currentLocation)) {
4165#if defined(Q_OS_UNIX)
4166 if (currentLocation == QDir::separator())
4167 return path.remove(i: 0, len: currentLocation.size());
4168#endif
4169 if (currentLocation.endsWith(c: u'/'))
4170 return path.remove(i: 0, len: currentLocation.size());
4171 else
4172 return path.remove(i: 0, len: currentLocation.size()+1);
4173 }
4174 return index.data(arole: QFileSystemModel::FilePathRole).toString();
4175}
4176
4177QStringList QFSCompleter::splitPath(const QString &path) const
4178{
4179 if (path.isEmpty())
4180 return QStringList(completionPrefix());
4181
4182 QString pathCopy = QDir::toNativeSeparators(pathName: path);
4183 QChar sep = QDir::separator();
4184#if defined(Q_OS_WIN)
4185 if (pathCopy == "\\"_L1 || pathCopy == "\\\\"_L1)
4186 return QStringList(pathCopy);
4187 QString doubleSlash("\\\\"_L1);
4188 if (pathCopy.startsWith(doubleSlash))
4189 pathCopy = pathCopy.mid(2);
4190 else
4191 doubleSlash.clear();
4192#elif defined(Q_OS_UNIX)
4193 {
4194 QString tildeExpanded = qt_tildeExpansion(path: pathCopy);
4195 if (tildeExpanded != pathCopy) {
4196 QFileSystemModel *dirModel;
4197 if (proxyModel)
4198 dirModel = qobject_cast<QFileSystemModel *>(object: proxyModel->sourceModel());
4199 else
4200 dirModel = sourceModel;
4201 dirModel->fetchMore(parent: dirModel->index(path: tildeExpanded));
4202 }
4203 pathCopy = std::move(tildeExpanded);
4204 }
4205#endif
4206
4207#if defined(Q_OS_WIN)
4208 QStringList parts = pathCopy.split(sep, Qt::SkipEmptyParts);
4209 if (!doubleSlash.isEmpty() && !parts.isEmpty())
4210 parts[0].prepend(doubleSlash);
4211 if (pathCopy.endsWith(sep))
4212 parts.append(QString());
4213#else
4214 QStringList parts = pathCopy.split(sep);
4215 if (pathCopy[0] == sep) // read the "/" at the beginning as the split removed it
4216 parts[0] = sep;
4217#endif
4218
4219#if defined(Q_OS_WIN)
4220 bool startsFromRoot = !parts.isEmpty() && parts[0].endsWith(u':');
4221#else
4222 bool startsFromRoot = pathCopy[0] == sep;
4223#endif
4224 if (parts.size() == 1 || (parts.size() > 1 && !startsFromRoot)) {
4225 const QFileSystemModel *dirModel;
4226 if (proxyModel)
4227 dirModel = qobject_cast<const QFileSystemModel *>(object: proxyModel->sourceModel());
4228 else
4229 dirModel = sourceModel;
4230 QString currentLocation = QDir::toNativeSeparators(pathName: dirModel->rootPath());
4231#if defined(Q_OS_WIN)
4232 if (currentLocation.endsWith(u':'))
4233 currentLocation.append(sep);
4234#endif
4235 if (currentLocation.contains(c: sep) && path != currentLocation) {
4236 QStringList currentLocationList = splitPath(path: currentLocation);
4237 while (!currentLocationList.isEmpty() && parts.size() > 0 && parts.at(i: 0) == ".."_L1) {
4238 parts.removeFirst();
4239 currentLocationList.removeLast();
4240 }
4241 if (!currentLocationList.isEmpty() && currentLocationList.constLast().isEmpty())
4242 currentLocationList.removeLast();
4243 return currentLocationList + parts;
4244 }
4245 }
4246 return parts;
4247}
